1
00:00:02,359 --> 00:00:32,097
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sama Sambhodasa Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sama Sambhodasa Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sama Sambhodasa Homage to the Buddha, the blessed, noble and fully self-awakened one.

2
00:00:33,561 --> 00:00:51,466
So I thought today, being the new year and everybody's made these amazing new year resolutions, that we would do the four bases of power or better still, the better translation, the four bases that lead to success.

3
00:00:52,607 --> 00:00:57,594
Now, these are part of the 37 requisites for awakening.

4
00:00:57,777 --> 00:00:59,439
the Bodhi Pakiya Dhamma.

5
00:01:00,280 --> 00:01:03,442
And this is the practice that the Buddha teaches us.

6
00:01:03,523 --> 00:01:06,447
So it begins with the four foundations of mindfulness.

7
00:01:07,768 --> 00:01:09,329
And then you have the four right efforts.

8
00:01:09,370 --> 00:01:10,531
I won't go into details.

9
00:01:10,631 --> 00:01:11,311
It takes too long.

10
00:01:12,013 --> 00:01:16,378
Then you get these four roads to success or basis for success.

11
00:01:17,478 --> 00:01:19,400
Then you have the spiritual faculties.

12
00:01:20,322 --> 00:01:25,388
And when you achieve stream entrant, they become the five spiritual powers.

13
00:01:25,957 --> 00:01:33,307
Then you have the seven factors of awakening, the Noble Eightfold Path, and all that adds up to 37.

14
00:01:34,408 --> 00:01:48,304
And according to Bhikkhu Thanissaro, Ajahn Thanissaro, some of you will know his very good work, he reckons that this relates to the 37 chords

15
00:01:48,959 --> 00:01:50,060
of those times.

16
00:01:50,721 --> 00:01:59,289
If you wanted to play the veena, which was like a guitar, then you had to be able to find these 37 chords.

17
00:02:00,349 --> 00:02:02,871
I don't know, I've never seen proof of that, but there we are.

18
00:02:03,533 --> 00:02:06,596
So there's a nice connection there between music and the Buddha Dhamma.

19
00:02:07,936 --> 00:02:13,801
Anyway, when you practice these four bases, you get what's known as the iddhis, or the powers.

20
00:02:16,805 --> 00:02:18,747
You might have heard them called the siddhis.

21
00:02:19,925 --> 00:02:21,167
So you can bilocate.

22
00:02:21,447 --> 00:02:24,032
You can appear in two different places or more.

23
00:02:25,354 --> 00:02:27,777
You can fly through the air and through walls.

24
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:35,711
You can have the divine eye where you see beyond what's possible through the physical body.

25
00:02:36,532 --> 00:02:38,194
And the same with the divine ear.

26
00:02:38,294 --> 00:02:45,526
You can hear things which you can't hear if the mind is constrained by the physical body.

27
00:02:45,641 --> 00:02:47,425
You can read other people's minds.

28
00:02:47,665 --> 00:02:52,533
You can see how people are born and die depending on their karma.

29
00:02:52,693 --> 00:02:54,417
So these are just some of them.

30
00:02:54,437 --> 00:02:57,361
Now, all these are very wonderful and magical.

31
00:02:57,983 --> 00:03:06,818
But the really important one for us is that it leads to the destruction of the mental defilements.

32
00:03:07,639 --> 00:03:09,843
So that's where they become important for us.

33
00:03:10,481 --> 00:03:17,192
So these four bases or four qualities are what we need in order to purify the heart.

34
00:03:17,733 --> 00:03:22,259
And that's an absolute necessity in order to become fully liberated.

35
00:03:24,483 --> 00:03:27,106
Okay, so what are these four bases?

36
00:03:28,049 --> 00:03:32,254
The first one is chanda, and it translates as desire.

37
00:03:32,335 --> 00:03:37,143
Now, in the dependent origination, of course, we have this word tanha.

38
00:03:37,163 --> 00:03:39,747
That's always an unwholesome desire.

39
00:03:39,766 --> 00:03:44,633
It's always a desire which is driven by greed, hatred or delusion.

40
00:03:45,395 --> 00:03:48,460
Chanda can be unskillful.

41
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:52,064
But here, of course, it's a skillful desire.

42
00:03:52,163 --> 00:03:55,812
Now, it's not just a wish, it's an aspiration.

43
00:03:56,532 --> 00:03:59,419
It's a longing, it's a yearning for something, right?

44
00:04:00,002 --> 00:04:06,897
So in order to get this liberation from suffering, you've got to really want it, okay?

45
00:04:08,887 --> 00:04:24,685
Now, once you've got that desire, once you've got that aspiration, the next thing that arises to support that, of course, is your energy, your commitment, true grit, you know, doggedness, perseverance and all that drive.

46
00:04:26,673 --> 00:04:32,480
And then with that, there comes a devotion to it.

47
00:04:32,901 --> 00:04:34,122
So that word is citta.

48
00:04:34,221 --> 00:04:38,567
Now, citta refers to both the heart and the mind.

49
00:04:38,728 --> 00:04:41,591
In other words, it's the whole mental process.

50
00:04:42,713 --> 00:04:47,678
And it demands a complete devotion from the heart to the task in hand.

51
00:04:47,759 --> 00:04:51,903
It's to do with attitude, dedication, devotion, care.

52
00:04:52,423 --> 00:05:05,742
And this is where the Buddha's word, appamado, one of his favorite words, which means diligence, is one of the last two words, appamado sampadita, you know, really strive, really work for your liberation.

53
00:05:06,497 --> 00:05:08,259
So there's the citta.

54
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:25,644
And then finally, there's this word vimamsa, which translates as discrimination, reflection, knowing what you're doing, constantly reflecting on how you feel, what you're doing, what the process is, where you're going, et cetera, et cetera.

55
00:05:26,444 --> 00:05:31,932
So these four qualities, I'm sure all of you have exercised these.

56
00:05:31,911 --> 00:05:39,788
They are necessary for spiritual attainment, but they're necessary for anything that you set about in ordinary daily life.

57
00:05:40,370 --> 00:05:50,932
You know, if you set yourself a goal, whatever it is, even if it's a simple thing like, you know, having to replant the garden or a job of work.

58
00:05:50,913 --> 00:05:54,278
You know, you've got to have these qualities.

59
00:05:54,478 --> 00:06:01,290
And if one of them is missing or if one of them is not up to standard, then it undermines the project.

60
00:06:01,391 --> 00:06:04,254
It'll undermine your process.

61
00:06:06,619 --> 00:06:08,802
Let's see now.

62
00:06:09,762 --> 00:06:12,005
I'm just thinking of my own personal.

63
00:06:12,045 --> 00:06:16,713
There's about four or five times in my life where I've had to put some special effort in.

64
00:06:17,754 --> 00:06:19,377
One of them was when I was a student.

65
00:06:20,098 --> 00:06:22,882
So I just lived the good old student life.

66
00:06:23,322 --> 00:06:28,310
And I was doing at the time this combination of a BA with a teacher's certificate.

67
00:06:28,290 --> 00:06:35,509
And in that very same year, they'd actually instituted the Bachelor of Education, which would have been far easier.

68
00:06:35,550 --> 00:06:42,166
Anyway, by the time I got to the fourth year, I knew I actually knew nothing.

69
00:06:42,988 --> 00:06:45,033
I had to pull my socks up, as they say.

70
00:06:45,132 --> 00:06:54,225
And I really, really, really wanted that BA because, you know, it's a passport to jobs and all sorts of stuff, especially in teaching.

71
00:06:55,048 --> 00:06:57,271
So I really had to put my heart and soul into it.

72
00:06:57,310 --> 00:07:02,178
And I remember working 12, 14 hours a day trying to get this stuff into my head.

73
00:07:03,922 --> 00:07:05,163
But what was missing there?

74
00:07:05,264 --> 00:07:07,767
So I had the desire, I had the aspiration.

75
00:07:07,848 --> 00:07:09,670
I really, really wanted that BA.

76
00:07:10,271 --> 00:07:12,355
I had the energy because I was young anyway.

77
00:07:12,622 --> 00:07:15,326
I had the energy, the empowerment to do it.

78
00:07:15,887 --> 00:07:18,129
My heart was completely devoted to it.

79
00:07:18,490 --> 00:07:21,334
But I'm also sure about the discrimination and reflection.

80
00:07:21,935 --> 00:07:26,822
So in those days, I don't remember anybody teaching you study skills or anything like that.

81
00:07:26,922 --> 00:07:30,266
You just sort of hung on in there and drove it in.

82
00:07:31,889 --> 00:07:37,096
If I'd have had some sort of guidance on study skills, it probably would have been that much easier for me.

83
00:07:37,697 --> 00:07:40,721
So I wasn't really reflecting on the ways

84
00:07:41,038 --> 00:07:45,322
that I was studying or the way that I had chosen to do this work.

85
00:07:46,103 --> 00:07:50,288
And it probably led to inefficiencies and all sorts of stuff.

86
00:07:51,329 --> 00:08:01,038
So I think if you look back into your life, I think you'll find there were times when you really had to put your body and soul into something, right?

87
00:08:01,398 --> 00:08:05,541
I use soul, of course, in a Buddhist sense.

88
00:08:07,223 --> 00:08:08,564
So here we have...

89
00:08:09,507 --> 00:08:11,892
Here we have these four qualities, okay?

90
00:08:12,374 --> 00:08:16,944
You have to have an aspiration, a yearning, a real zeal for something.

91
00:08:17,386 --> 00:08:22,077
And there has to come that energy, which includes a sort of diligence.

92
00:08:22,699 --> 00:08:24,863
Your heart has to be right behind it.

93
00:08:25,305 --> 00:08:27,651
And there's this constant reflection.

94
00:08:27,697 --> 00:08:33,027
So in our spiritual life, every day, you see, there's that.

95
00:08:34,089 --> 00:08:42,624
Every time you wake up in the morning to set yourself to make this a day of mindfulness, affectionate mindfulness.

96
00:08:43,264 --> 00:08:46,191
I mean, that's what the Buddha wants us to do.

97
00:08:46,772 --> 00:08:51,580
That's his teaching in the Betta Sutta, the discourse on goodwill.

98
00:08:51,559 --> 00:08:58,592
to develop not just a mindfulness, but something that engages also the heart.

99
00:08:59,193 --> 00:09:01,597
And that's your sense of care.

100
00:09:02,178 --> 00:09:03,881
So it's care and attention.

101
00:09:04,123 --> 00:09:08,691
Care and attention leads to this affectionate mindfulness.

102
00:09:09,464 --> 00:09:14,432
And sometimes you have to give yourself a really good aspiration.

103
00:09:14,491 --> 00:09:23,044
So the aspiration, whatever it is, the end of suffering, make life a bit easier, movement towards contentment, it's better for other people.

104
00:09:24,466 --> 00:09:27,552
You can always bring others in.

105
00:09:27,871 --> 00:09:34,942
And then to raise that energy, the commitment to your practice, and then this constant reflection.

106
00:09:35,583 --> 00:09:38,187
So throughout the day when the mind's wandering,

107
00:09:38,422 --> 00:09:41,005
You find yourself all over the place just to stop for a minute.

108
00:09:41,046 --> 00:09:42,048
Whoa, where am I going?

109
00:09:42,107 --> 00:09:42,908
What am I doing?

110
00:09:43,570 --> 00:09:47,937
And in that way, we're slowly developing these qualities, right?

111
00:09:47,956 --> 00:09:50,541
And well, that's the path.

112
00:09:50,581 --> 00:09:53,186
I mean, it's pretty straightforward, really, once you're into it.

113
00:09:54,927 --> 00:09:57,552
So that's what I've got for this evening.

114
00:09:57,793 --> 00:10:01,678
And it supports whatever resolutions you've made.

115
00:10:01,698 --> 00:10:05,424
So a resolution normally lasts for as long as you say it, right?

116
00:10:06,653 --> 00:10:12,981
So it's no good saying, oh, you know, I won't have any tea from now on.

117
00:10:13,442 --> 00:10:15,645
It'll last about 10 minutes, right?

118
00:10:15,666 --> 00:10:21,995
So you've got to keep reinforcing that commitment, whatever your resolution has been.

119
00:10:22,056 --> 00:10:24,659
Okay.

120
00:10:24,679 --> 00:10:24,779
Okay.

121
00:10:26,582 --> 00:10:27,063
Very good.

122
00:10:27,124 --> 00:10:27,784
Short and sweet.

123
00:10:28,306 --> 00:10:43,748
I hope these words have been of some assistance that I have not caused confusion and that by your devotion to the practice and the four bases of success, you will be liberated from all suffering sooner rather than later.

